;W[rr]LB[qr:1][pq:2][rr:3][sq:A]C[Diagram 1 (Correct)


White 1 is a good starting point. If you can find this move, there is no way you will get this problem wrong.

Black 2 is unavoidable. Black has to avoid the snapback.

White connects at 3 and black is dead. Now even if black connects at \b\f1 A\b0\f0 , it does no good.
