;W[pq]LB[rr:1][pq:2]CR[qr]C[Diagram 2 (Snapback)


This is a variant of the correct answer.
As mentioned before, in response to white \'a1\'e2 if black tries to resist and cuts with 1, white creates a snapback at 2.

In this case, black is also dead.

As soon as black suffers the blow of white \'a1\'e2, black has no way to live.
